                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>A <material>white marble</material>
                              <objectType>panel-stele</objectType> (<dimensions><height unit="metre">0.88</height> <width unit="metre">0.64</width> <depth unit="metre">0.21</depth></dimensions>). 
                              The relief is of a nude facing <rs type="decoration">gladiator</rs>, who still wears arm-protectors on his right upper arm, and shin-guards. 
                              He holds a palm with his right arm, which is partly lost; his left arm is stretched out horizontally, and the hand rests on a helmet placed on 
                              what is either a smooth column or a tall shield. Below are two small figures: that on the man's right has shin-guards and a long shield, and looks up at him; 
                              that on his left is winged and naked, and holds his right arm down, and left arm raised, while regarding the central figure. For a full description see Kontokosta (2008).</p>
                        </support>
